# Exo:
As part of the migration, there were some components added to the AWS account. 
The team created one of the EC2 instances where they need to make some changes now.

## Requirements:
There is an EC2 instance named xfusion-ec2 under us-east-1 region, enable the stop protection for this instance

# Solution:
1-  Go to EC2 Dashboard and Click on Instances running in resource section
2- Select `xfusion-ec2` instance and Click on Actions in the top menu, then hover over Instance settings and select Change stop protection.
3- In the configuration dialog, check the Enable box.
4- Save the new configuration.
